                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Bulgaria)/11–1744:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Mr. <persName type="to">Alexander C. Kirk</persName>, Political Adviser,
                        Allied Force Headquarters at Caserta</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-23T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 23, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>419. Your 1356, November 17, 9 p.m.<note n="58" xml:id="d428fn58">Not
                        printed.</note> Department is informed by Joint Chiefs that Major General
                    John A. Crane was designated on November 17 as Chief of United States Military
                    Representation on the Allied Control Commission for Bulgaria. He has been
                    ordered to proceed to Sofia from Caserta as soon as possible. Two additional <pb
                        facs="0502" n="490" xml:id="pg_490"/> Army members and a Navy member will
                    shortly be designated and ordered to Sofia. Please inform Barnes.</p>
                <p>Sent to Caserta, repeated to London and Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
